Name: (+)-Oxypeucedanin
Description: (+)-oxypeucedanin is a furanocoumarin. It has a role as a metabolite.

plant_concentrations.References: (1) Chaudhary SK et al; Planta Med 6: 462-4 (1986) (2) Numonov S et al; Nat Prod Res 32: 2325-32 (2018) (3) Mileski KS et al; J Agric Food Chem 65: 10933-49 (2017) (4) Razavi SM et al; Nat Prod Res 29: 2037-40 (2015) (5) Tavakoli S et al; Nat Prod Res 27: 1-5 (2017)
plant_concentrations.Value: Oxypeucedanin was detected at 70-100 ppm wet weight in parsley (Petroselinum crispum)(1). Oxypeucedanin was found in the roots of Prangos pabularia(2), Angelica pancicii Vandas (Apiaceae)(3), Ferulag angulata Boiss(4) and Ferulag trifida Boiss (Apiaceae)(5).
